status: MARC21-007: Form of composition for music

definition (en): Canons and rounds. Compositions employing strict imitation throughout.

scope note (en): Includes music for individual dances except for mazurkas, minuets, pavans, polonaises, and waltzes.

preferred label (en): divertimentos, serenades, cassations, divertissements, and notturni
definition (en): Divertimentos, serenades, cassations, divertissements, and notturni.

scope note (en): All the Flamenco styles, or "palos", and other forms of song and dance coming from the folkloric tradition of Spanish gypsies.
Used for any item that is a non-music sound recording.
Includes all types of ostinato basses.

definition (en): Spanish and Spanish American theatre music.

scope note (en): Used when the only indication given is the number of instruments and the medium of performance. No structure or genre is given, although they may be implied or understood.

definition (en): Characteristic form of Spanish polyphony, religious or secular, from the 16th to 18th centuries. Religious villancicos were usually sung in important ceremonies (including Christmas, when these songs were sometimes called "pastoradas").
